README.md
     1‚Üí# dotenv [![NPM version](https://img.shields.io/npm/v/dotenv.svg?style=flat-square)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/dotenv) [![downloads](https://img.shields.io/npm/dw/dotenv)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/dotenv)
     2‚Üí
     3‚Üí<img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/motdotla/dotenv/master/dotenv.svg" alt="dotenv" align="right" width="200" />
     4‚Üí
     5‚ÜíDotenv is a zero-dependency module that loads environment variables from a `.env` file into [`process.env`](https://nodejs.org/docs/latest/api/process.html#process_process_env). Storing configuration in the environment separate from code is based on [The Twelve-Factor App](https://12factor.net/config) methodology.
     6‚Üí
     7‚Üí[Watch the tutorial](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YtkZR0NFd1g)
     8‚Üí
     9‚Üí&nbsp;
    10‚Üí
    11‚Üí## Usage
    12‚Üí
    13‚ÜíInstall it.
    14‚Üí
    15‚Üí```sh
    16‚Üínpm install dotenv --save
    17‚Üí```
    18‚Üí
    19‚ÜíCreate a `.env` file in the root of your project:
    20‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
    39‚Üí## Advanced
    40‚Üí
    41‚Üí<details><summary>ES6</summary><br>
    42‚Üí
