    44‚Üí
    45‚Üí```javascript
    46‚Üíimport 'dotenv/config'
    47‚Üí```
    48‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   319‚Üí## Agents
   320‚Üí
   321‚Üí<img src="https://dotenvx.com/assets/img/as2/9.jpg" height="400" alt="dotenvx-as2" align="right"/>
   322‚Üí
   323‚Üí> Software is changing, and dotenv must change with it‚Äîthat is why I built [agentic secret storage (AS2)](https://dotenvx.com/as2). Agents run code without humans at terminals, so plaintext `.env` files are the wrong primitive.
   324‚Üí>
   325‚Üí> AS2 is built for autonomous software: encrypted by default, zero console access, and cryptography‚Äëfirst delivery that keeps operators out of the loop.
   326‚Üí>
   327‚Üí> It is backed by [Vestauth](https://github.com/vestauth/vestauth), the trusted, pioneering auth layer for agents‚Äîgiving each agent a cryptographic identity so requests are signed with private keys and verified with public keys. No shared secrets to leak.
   328‚Üí>
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   331‚Üí### Quickstart
   332‚Üí
   333‚ÜíInstall vestauth and initialize your agent.
   334‚Üí
   335‚Üí```bash
   336‚Üínpm i -g vestauth
   337‚Üí
   338‚Üívestauth agent init
   339‚Üí```
   340‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   357‚Üí## FAQ
   358‚Üí
